OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1781449872
OL,3,CNew sensor could detect arthritis
OL,4,Cbefore major joint damage occurs
OL,6,FUniversity of Brighton researchers are
OL,7,Fdeveloping a first-of-its-kind sensor
OL,8,Fthat could detect osteoarthritis
OL,9,Fbefore irreversible joint damage
OL,10,Foccurs.
OL,12,FIt opena new possibilities for earlier
OL,13,Fdiagnosis, treatment, and prevention.
OL,15,FWork on a pioneering new sensor could
OL,16,Ftransform how osteoarthritis is
OL,17,Fdiagnosed, by detecting the disease
OL,18,Fbefore lasting damage is visible on
OL,19,Fscans or symptoms become severe.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/8
