OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1781449872
OL,3,CNew sensor could detect arthritis
OL,4,Cbefore major joint damage occurs
OL,6,FThe team is developing a sensor
OL,7,Fdesigned to detect tiny chemical
OL,8,Fchanges in joint fluid that may signal
OL,9,Fthe earliest signs of osteoarthritis,
OL,10,Flong before damage can be seen through
OL,11,Fcurrent diagnostic methods.
OL,13,FBy identifying these early warning
OL,14,Fsigns, researchers hope the technology
OL,15,Fcould eventually help clinicians
OL,16,Fdiagnose the condition sooner, monitor
OL,17,Fhow it progresses, and intervene
OL,18,Fbefore joints become permanently
OL,19,Fdamaged.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1781449872
OL,3,CNew sensor could detect arthritis
OL,4,Cbefore major joint damage occurs
OL,6,FThe project builds on new sensing
OL,7,Ftechnology originally developed by
OL,8,FProfessor Patel and his team for other
OL,9,Fbiological applications.
OL,11,FThis will be the first time the
OL,12,Ftechnology has been adapted and tested
OL,13,Fin osteoarthritis research.
OL,15,FProfessor Staines said: "At the
OL,16,Fmoment, osteoarthritis is often
OL,17,Fdiagnosed only after significant and
OL,18,Firreversible joint damage has already
OL,19,Foccurred.
OL,21,F"We want to change that.
OL,26,@wD@YOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1781449872
OL,3,CNew sensor could detect arthritis
OL,4,Cbefore major joint damage occurs
OL,6,F"By combining expertise in skeletal
OL,7,Fbiology and sensor technology, we have
OL,8,Fan opportunity to detect the earliest
OL,9,Fchanges linked to osteoarthritis
OL,10,Fbefore lasting damage takes hold.
OL,12,F"If successful, this could open the
OL,13,Fdoor to earlier diagnosis, better
OL,14,Fmonitoring of disease progression, and
OL,15,Fultimately improved quality of life
OL,16,Ffor millions of people living with
OL,17,Fjoint disease."
OL,19,FResearchers will begin by testing the
OL,20,Fsensor using synovial fluid.
OL,26,@tD@AOUyD@OO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
